 SEGUN AYINDE, ABEOKUTA Police in Ogun have arrested three self-acclaimed Islamic clerics, who specialize in defrauding unsuspecting members of the public their money and having carnal knowledge of their female victims. The suspects, Aliu Abdulfatai, 50, Sule Adebayo, 36, and Leland Olokodana, 31, were arrested following a complaint by a female victim(Name withheld) at Adigbe police station that she was defrauded of the sum of N70,000 by the suspects and was subsequently forcefully raped by one of them. The Police Public Relations Officer, Abimbola Oyeyemi said that the victim, who is a marketer with a popular Property/Real estate company, was said to be on marketing assignment when she came across the suspects, who claimed to be Islamic clerics and indicated interest in purchasing large expanse of land which they claimed they wanted to use for construction of their mosque. Oyeyemi said that the suspects introduced special prayer for their victim and saw allegedly gave her a purported vision that she was under a spell which needed special deliverance prayer to be cast out. The victim said in the course of performing the deliverance on her, they succeeded in fraudulently obtaining the sum of N70,000 from her and they later lured her into their house where one of them forcefully had carnal knowledge of her. The PPRO said that on the strength of her complaint, the DPO of Adigbe division, CSP Augustine Opadile detailed his detectives to go after the hoodlums and bring them to justice. He said the detectivesâ€™ efforts paid off when three amongst the suspects were nabbed when they were waiting for the victim to bring the money they demanded from her while one of them escaped. Oyeyemi said that on interrogation, they confessed being fraudsters who have been defrauding people to survive as one of them also confessed that he used the proceed of their fraudulent activities to build a private school in Ikorodu, Lagos State. Meanwhile, the Commissioner of Police, CP Bashir Makama has ordered a full scale investigation into the activities of the hoodlums with the view to charge them to court as soon as possible. 